Add comprehensive CI/CD and testing scripts for VishwamAI
- Implement `run_full_test.sh` to orchestrate the full testing workflow, including environment setup, resource management, test execution, result aggregation, report generation, and visualization. - Create `cleanup_ci_cd.sh` for managing CI/CD environment cleanup, including secret rotation and resource deletion. - Develop `maintain_ci_cd.sh` for routine maintenance tasks such as checking resource quotas, cleaning old resources, and verifying configuration. - Introduce `setup_ci_cd.sh` to automate the setup of the CI/CD environment, including Google Cloud configuration and GitHub secrets management. - Add `setup_test_env.sh` for preparing the testing environment with necessary dependencies for TPU, GPU, and CPU platforms. - Establish `pytest.ini` for configuring pytest test discovery and execution. - Create `setup.py` for managing test dependencies and package installation. - Implement `visualize_test_results.py` for generating visualizations of test results and performance metrics. - Ensure all scripts include error handling, logging, and user prompts for better usability.

Add comprehensive test suite for VishwamAI kernels
- Introduced a structured test suite in the `tests` directory for VishwamAI kernels across TPU, GPU, and CPU platforms. - Created a README.md file detailing setup instructions, test organization, and performance benchmarks. - Implemented pytest configuration in `conftest.py` to manage platform-specific test requirements and device availability checks. - Developed a test runner script (`run_tests.py`) to facilitate running tests with various configurations. - Added unit and integration tests in `test_kernels.py` covering matrix operations, attention mechanisms, layer operations, and optimizers. - Established a requirements file (`requirements-test.txt`) for managing test dependencies across platforms. - Implemented expert balancing utilities in `moe_balance.py` to optimize expert placement across devices.
